messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /printshop

- all HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The method handling this endpoint is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshop", method = RequestMethod.GET) (last handler in ManagerController). That explicitly maps the path "/printshop" and restricts the mapping to the GET HTTP method.
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping on ManagerController, so no additional prefix is applied; the full path is exactly "/printshop".
- Because the mapping explicitly specifies RequestMethod.GET, only GET is explicitly accepted by the code. Per the instruction to base acceptability on the code (not framework implicit behaviors), HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE and the other methods are not considered acceptable since they are not declared.
